{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014K8bHG9NWjaEoHPrAaLvHY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear: `elasticsearch-0` can only discover itself. It's looking for `elasticsearch-1` and `elasticsearch-2` but the StatefulSet hasn't created those pods yet because the StatefulSet is waiting for `elasticsearch-0` to become Ready first (it creates pods sequentially).\n\nThis is a classic chicken-and-egg problem with Elasticsearch clusters on StatefulSets:\n- StatefulSet only creates the next pod when the previous one is ready\n- `elasticsearch-0` won't be ready until it forms a cluster (because the readiness probe checks cluster health)\n- But forming a cluster requires the other nodes to exist\n\nThe fix is straightforward: set `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` in the StatefulSet spec so all pods are created simultaneously instead of sequentially. This is the standard approach for Elasticsearch deployments. The readiness probe will then work correctly once the cluster can actually form. Now I'll apply the parallel pod management policy to the StatefulSet.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9715,"cache_read_input_tokens":41454,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9715},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8db3a55-0d34-47f9-a2a1-261f430454c3","uuid":"6e65fca8-9c29-4c67-af0c-4782e04c35cb","request_id":"req_011CcLaLvYo3N4z3d8Xa3cBE"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014K8bHG9NWjaEoHPrAaLvHY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Root cause is clear: the StatefulSet creates pods sequentially, so `elasticsearch-1` and `elasticsearch-2` don't exist yet when `elasticsearch-0` tries to bootstrap. The fix is `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all 3 pods start simultaneously and can discover each other."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9715,"cache_read_input_tokens":41454,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":9715},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8db3a55-0d34-47f9-a2a1-261f430454c3","uuid":"75dc3da8-27e0-408e-ab44-c72a1a122616","request_id":"req_011CcLaLvYo3N4z3d8Xa3cBE"}
